cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of identifying highly correlated pairs in a collection of mostly pairwise uncorrelated random variables, which can be interpreted as a time-series. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.IT (information theory), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.SI (social and information networks), and cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing). The use of sketch techniques and coding theory also supports these potential sub-categories.
